Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gherad>Gherad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 610<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 5:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Masters of Versatile Damage?</span><hr size=1> Wizards are the masters of versatile nukes.  If you want someone to burn a mob with DD spells, a wizard will always work.  We are not the masters of versatile damage.  As Qaman pointed out, other classes like necros can do all 5 flavors of damage.  Bards also can do them all.<br>
<br>
